==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Dulse
<hw>Dulse</hw> <pr>(d⟦ucr⟧ls)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[Cf. Gael.
<ets>duileasg</ets>; <ets>duille</ets> leaf + <ets>uisge</ets> water.
Cf. <er>Whisky</er>.]</ety> <fld>(Bot.)</fld> <def>A seaweed of a
reddish brown color, which is sometimes eaten, as in Scotland. The true
dulse is <spn>Sarcophyllis edulis</spn>; the common is
<gen>Rhodymenia</gen>. <altsp>[Written also
<asp>dillisk.</asp>]</altsp></def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>The crimson leaf of the <qex>dulse</qex> is seen⟦br⟧
To blush like a banner bathed in slaughter.</q>
<rj><qau>Percival.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Dulwilly</ent>⟦br⟧
